3
00:01:31,752 --> 00:01:35,448
- [Both Grunting]
- [Man Shouting In Foreign Language]

4
00:01:38,022 --> 00:01:40,818
[Continues In Foreign Language]

5
00:01:50,337 --> 00:01:52,167
Intel confirmed.
Nine hostiles, three marines.

6
00:01:52,266 --> 00:01:55,060
[Man On Radio] Ghost Two, you are not
to engage. Alpha Team is on its way.

7
00:01:55,158 --> 00:01:57,855
No time.

8
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:04,383
[Shouting In Foreign Language]

9
00:02:11,267 --> 00:02:13,184
[Yelling]

10
00:02:46,922 --> 00:02:49,070
- You guys ready to go home?
- Yeah.

11
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:12,219
- How do we get around 'em?
- We don't.

12
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:17,844
We go through 'em.

13
00:03:21,322 --> 00:03:23,954
[Soldiers Shouting In Distance]

14
00:03:28,460 --> 00:03:31,025
[Man]
Atten-hut! Look sharp, marine.

15
00:03:31,128 --> 00:03:34,308
As you were, gentlemen.

16
00:03:34,406 --> 00:03:38,167
- Triton.
- Sir?

17
00:03:38,265 --> 00:03:40,896
Outside. Ten minutes.

18
00:03:40,999 --> 00:03:43,399
Yes, sir.

19
00:03:51,062 --> 00:03:54,142
[Man] We've approached
this thing from every angle.

20
00:03:54,245 --> 00:03:57,359
The judge advocate's done
hearing your case.

21
00:03:57,460 --> 00:04:00,771
- What about an appeal?
- They're not accepting more appeals.

22
00:04:02,154 --> 00:04:06,748
Bottom line is, you disobeyed a direct order.

23
00:04:06,848 --> 00:04:08,831
You're being discharged.

24
00:04:12,603 --> 00:04:16,036
You served your unit, your corps
and your country with honor, son.

25
00:04:16,141 --> 00:04:19,000
Walk away with dignity.

26
00:04:21,189 --> 00:04:23,689
Colonel...

27
00:04:23,793 --> 00:04:25,842
I'm a marine.

28
00:04:27,297 --> 00:04:30,860
One of the best. Remember that.

29
00:04:30,963 --> 00:04:35,653
On behalf of a grateful nation
and the United States Marine Corps...

30
00:04:35,752 --> 00:04:38,900
I thank you for your loyal service.

31
00:05:28,867 --> 00:05:31,597
- Thank you.
- Oh!

32
00:05:39,928 --> 00:05:41,757
You're home.

33
00:06:06,419 --> 00:06:08,731
- You all right?
- Yeah.

34
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:13,260
Yeah, I just- I can't believe you're here.

35
00:06:25,872 --> 00:06:29,115
You know, the hardest thing...

36
00:06:29,215 --> 00:06:32,546
about you leaving was not knowing.

37
00:06:33,908 --> 00:06:37,986
You know, not knowing
where you were...

38
00:06:38,089 --> 00:06:40,621
not knowing if you're coming home...

39
00:06:40,726 --> 00:06:45,285
not knowing if I'm gonna get
that phone call saying that you wouldn't be.

40
00:06:45,387 --> 00:06:48,083
You married a marine, Kate.

41
00:06:48,184 --> 00:06:51,549
I know it's not gonna be
easy for you, John.

42
00:06:51,656 --> 00:06:54,003
We'll figure it out together.

43
00:06:55,966 --> 00:06:59,144
I'm home now, and I'm not goin' anywhere.

44
00:06:59,244 --> 00:07:04,002
Good. And speaking of that...

45
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:05,931
are you sure about
starting this job tomorrow?

46
00:07:06,028 --> 00:07:09,722
- Oh!
- I just think there's so many
other things you could be doing.

47
00:07:09,821 --> 00:07:12,683
If I sat around here all day, I'd go insane.

48
00:07:14,324 --> 00:07:17,721
I just want you to be happy, John.

49
00:07:17,827 --> 00:07:20,294
I am happy. Come on.

50
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:24,030
- Oh! Geez. Where are we going?
- To make me happy.

51
00:07:37,056 --> 00:07:40,069
- I'll be right back.
- [Cuban Accent] You got it, man.

52
00:07:40,173 --> 00:07:42,004
What?

53
00:07:42,103 --> 00:07:45,215
You got it, man.
You know, Scarface. Come on.

54
00:07:45,317 --> 00:07:47,597
Do it again.

55
00:07:47,696 --> 00:07:49,561
Okay. You got it, man.

56
00:07:49,657 --> 00:07:52,289
Wow. That's horrible.

57
00:08:31,325 --> 00:08:33,573
[No Audible Dialogue]

58
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,565
- How you doing?
- Fine, sir.

59
00:09:13,926 --> 00:09:15,976
Excuse me.

60
00:09:16,082 --> 00:09:18,327
[Customers Screaming, Gasping]

61
00:09:20,935 --> 00:09:22,984
Everybody down.

62
00:09:24,504 --> 00:09:27,420
Everybody on the ground, now!

63
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:32,243
Ladies and gentlemen,
keep your heads down and your mouths shut.

64
00:09:32,348 --> 00:09:35,011
I don't wanna see any eye contact.

65
00:09:35,114 --> 00:09:37,614
I have severe intimacy issues and a gun...

66
00:09:37,719 --> 00:09:40,514
so do yourselves a favor
and don't look up.

67
00:09:44,407 --> 00:09:46,390
What I want is on
the other side of this door...

68
00:09:46,497 --> 00:09:51,736
but that's gonna be a little tricky
because... it's bulletproof.

69
00:09:51,834 --> 00:09:55,198
So here's how we're gonna do it.
Hi, honey. Can I borrow you for a second?

70
00:09:55,306 --> 00:09:56,905
[Screaming]

71
00:09:57,010 --> 00:09:59,893
- How you doin' in there, sport?
- [Woman] Oh, God! Please!

72
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:03,595
Oh, don't look at him.
He can't help you.

73
00:10:03,697 --> 00:10:05,713
Please! I have children!

74
00:10:05,818 --> 00:10:08,417
I don't think he cares.

75
00:10:08,519 --> 00:10:11,533
Please!
[Screams]

76
00:10:11,639 --> 00:10:14,500
[Beeping]

77
00:10:28,357 --> 00:10:31,052
Fill it.

78
00:10:37,842 --> 00:10:40,701
Get down!

79
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:57,840
Thank you.

80
00:10:57,937 --> 00:11:00,668
Rome.

81
00:11:01,955 --> 00:11:04,837
You gotta hit me.
It's gotta look real-

82
00:11:04,944 --> 00:11:06,895
For the cops.

83
00:11:15,552 --> 00:11:17,383
That's real.

84
00:11:20,729 --> 00:11:22,623
Well, the cops are comin'.

85
00:11:22,721 --> 00:11:25,967
I'd love to stay and chat,
but, uh, I can't.

86
00:11:26,066 --> 00:11:29,880
I apologize for that little
outburst of anger I showed earlier.

87
00:11:29,986 --> 00:11:32,266
That's really more for dramatic purposes
than anything else.

88
00:11:32,367 --> 00:11:36,063
I hope that what I've done here today
doesn't force you to have...

89
00:11:36,162 --> 00:11:40,973
a negative opinion of me or how you think
I feel about the great state of South Carolina.

90
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,425
'Cause I love it here. I do.

91
00:11:43,525 --> 00:11:46,155
I love the people.

92
00:11:46,257 --> 00:11:48,854
Enjoy the rest of your day.

93
00:11:59,856 --> 00:12:03,803
[Sirens Wailing In Distance]

94
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:45,061
What? Too much?

95
00:12:46,442 --> 00:12:48,492
[Tires Screeching]

96
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:56,055
Ooh!

97
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:11,133
Okay.

98
00:13:11,231 --> 00:13:13,665
We know how they got in here.

99
00:13:13,772 --> 00:13:16,535
Once they're in, they don't bother
with any small stuff.

100
00:13:16,634 --> 00:13:20,877
They just go right for the vault
with 12 million in diamonds in it.

101
00:13:20,974 --> 00:13:24,055
The same diamonds
that were delivered just 24 hours ago.

102
00:13:24,156 --> 00:13:27,237
What are the odds of that?

103
00:13:27,341 --> 00:13:29,554
And how did our guys know...

104
00:13:29,654 --> 00:13:31,935
that they were gonna get
so lucky today?

105
00:13:32,034 --> 00:13:34,830
We could ask our friend
on the floor over there.

106
00:13:34,928 --> 00:13:37,109
I'll bet he knows.

107
00:13:42,354 --> 00:13:44,339
[Chattering]

108
00:13:51,807 --> 00:13:53,672
I don't care.

109
00:13:53,769 --> 00:13:56,532
No, do you understand
what I'm saying? Oh, really?

110
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:59,645
See if you can understand this.

111
00:14:11,419 --> 00:14:13,699
[Chuckling]

112
00:14:17,851 --> 00:14:20,513
Is this what you do all day?

113
00:14:20,614 --> 00:14:23,114
Hmm? I had a Game Boy...

114
00:14:23,219 --> 00:14:25,050
but they took it.

115
00:14:32,961 --> 00:14:36,392
Come on, man. This is a great job.

116
00:14:36,498 --> 00:14:39,359
Good benefits. Great money.

117
00:14:39,456 --> 00:14:42,340
A couple two, three years,
they move you to management.

118
00:14:43,732 --> 00:14:45,562
How long you been working here?

119
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:47,493
Nine years.

120
00:14:48,780 --> 00:14:50,610
How come you're not in management?

121
00:14:52,606 --> 00:14:56,004
[Phone Ringing]

122
00:14:56,110 --> 00:14:57,645
Security.

123
00:14:59,454 --> 00:15:03,433
We'll be right there.
Psycho ex-boyfriend on 12.

124
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:09,417
Rick, have you lost your mind?
This is my job.

125
00:15:09,518 --> 00:15:12,083
Oh, really? It doesn't
look like a whorehouse.

126
00:15:12,186 --> 00:15:14,498
Where's all the other whores?
Where's your pimp?

127
00:15:14,598 --> 00:15:18,226
You were with him. That's the reason you
didn't answer your cell phone all weekend!

128
00:15:18,326 --> 00:15:20,409
Sir, could you please come with us?

129
00:15:20,513 --> 00:15:22,498
Don't mess with me, pork chop.

130
00:15:22,603 --> 00:15:24,652
- "Pork chop"?
- You're causing a scene.

131
00:15:24,758 --> 00:15:28,769
You think this is a scene? Wait till I tell
Daddy about the little whore he raised!

132
00:15:28,872 --> 00:15:31,921
- Sir, I'm just gonna have to ask you-
- Ask me to what?

133
00:15:32,024 --> 00:15:36,517
- Take a seat, flattop. I'll get to you in a second.
- Oh, really?

134
00:15:36,620 --> 00:15:41,049
Get your hands off me!
Why are you so angry?

135
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:46,389
[Cell Phone Ringing]

136
00:15:46,492 --> 00:15:50,340
You got the Drake.
Dude, let me call you back later.

137
00:15:50,447 --> 00:15:52,495
Because I am trapped in an elevator...

138
00:15:52,599 --> 00:15:54,551
- with a couple of jackasses, that's why!
- [Elevator Bell Dings]

139
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,974
We kindly ask you
to leave the premises, sir.

140
00:16:05,268 --> 00:16:07,581
Thanks.

141
00:16:11,184 --> 00:16:15,393
Seriously, just spit-balling here.
Tell me if I'm close.

142
00:16:15,492 --> 00:16:18,769
Right out of high school,
straight into the military?

143
00:16:18,868 --> 00:16:21,598
Realized you'd never be
all you thought you could be...

144
00:16:21,696 --> 00:16:24,613
and that's how you ended up
as a rent-a-cop.

145
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:27,602
Tell me I'm wrong.

146
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:31,528
Whoa! Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hey, wait a minute. Wait a minute.

147
00:16:31,633 --> 00:16:34,515
- The genie tried to hit me!
- I know. I saw that,
and he shouldn't have done that.

148
00:16:34,622 --> 00:16:37,670
You shouldn't have done that.
But he missed, and you're fine.

149
00:16:37,773 --> 00:16:40,952
We deal with people like this every day,
and in order to avoid an incident...

150
00:16:41,053 --> 00:16:42,883
sometimes you just
gotta let things go.

151
00:16:42,982 --> 00:16:46,742
Yeah? Well, you better
tell your boyfriend to back off.

152
00:16:46,841 --> 00:16:50,786
Unfortunately for the genie,
this is not one of those times.

153
00:17:09,217 --> 00:17:11,398
Oh!

154
00:17:11,499 --> 00:17:13,812
[Gasping]

155
00:17:15,357 --> 00:17:19,084
It's on now. See, you really messed up.

156
00:17:19,183 --> 00:17:21,782
Somewhere, somehow,
somebody just got all this on video.

157
00:17:23,524 --> 00:17:26,670
By the time you go to sleep tonight,
I'm gonna own this building.

158
00:17:26,771 --> 00:17:29,655
And tomorrow...

159
00:17:29,762 --> 00:17:32,162
don't be late.

160
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:36,149
'Cause when you clock in, you're fired!

161
00:17:53,457 --> 00:17:55,290
Johnny.

162
00:17:59,918 --> 00:18:01,837
[Clears Throat]
A toast.

163
00:18:01,944 --> 00:18:04,926
To your first and last day on the job.

164
00:18:05,032 --> 00:18:07,729
[Chuckles]
Yeah.

165
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:10,076
- About that-
- Dude, I told you, don't worry about it.

166
00:18:10,176 --> 00:18:12,576
It's not the first time
I've been suspended.

167
00:18:12,685 --> 00:18:15,798
That's not it. Um-

168
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:18,728
You'll find another job.
You got all that training.

169
00:18:18,824 --> 00:18:21,138
Training.

170
00:18:21,237 --> 00:18:24,700
Covert reconnaissance.
Close-quarter hand-to-hand combat.

171
00:18:24,805 --> 00:18:26,634
Demolition.

172
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:29,046
Not a high call in the workplace
for skills like that, Joe.

173
00:18:29,145 --> 00:18:32,675
Okay, but you're a smart guy.
You can do whatever you want.

174
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:35,245
You don't get it. It's not-

175
00:18:35,349 --> 00:18:38,365
It's not about work.
It's not about a job.

176
00:18:38,470 --> 00:18:40,420
Being a marine meant everything to me.

177
00:18:43,420 --> 00:18:47,564
Now I go and get fired
from some bullshit security job.

178
00:18:47,664 --> 00:18:50,579
Sorry.

179
00:18:50,685 --> 00:18:52,801
I don't know what to do.

180
00:18:54,930 --> 00:18:57,145
Look.

181
00:18:57,245 --> 00:19:01,357
I'm not gonna try and pretend
I know what you're going through...

182
00:19:01,458 --> 00:19:03,353
'cause I don't.

183
00:19:05,091 --> 00:19:09,169
And-And your time as a marine-
Yeah, it's over.

184
00:19:09,271 --> 00:19:12,284
And that sucks, man.

185
00:19:12,388 --> 00:19:14,221
But your life's not over.

186
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:16,751
I mean, it's changing...

187
00:19:16,858 --> 00:19:18,754
but you gotta learn to change with it.

188
00:19:21,294 --> 00:19:23,443
Sometimes-

189
00:19:23,545 --> 00:19:28,073
Sometimes, it's good to just take
a step back and see what you still have.

190
00:19:32,612 --> 00:19:36,207
You know, I think I'm gonna
go home and see my wife.

191
00:19:36,310 --> 00:19:38,425
Yeah. She's hot.

192
00:19:49,138 --> 00:19:51,483
What happened today?

193
00:19:56,854 --> 00:20:00,220
We made a lot of money.

194
00:20:00,328 --> 00:20:02,926
In the vault... with the kid.

195
00:20:04,506 --> 00:20:06,907
That kid showed that
he couldn't keep his mouth shut.

196
00:20:07,013 --> 00:20:11,125
And Morgan blowin' up that cop car?

197
00:20:11,226 --> 00:20:13,375
He went a little overboard.

198
00:20:13,476 --> 00:20:15,756
But in all fairness to Morgan...

199
00:20:15,855 --> 00:20:19,385
I was firing an automatic weapon at those cops.

200
00:20:19,488 --> 00:20:22,855
Dead cops, all those witnesses-

201
00:20:22,962 --> 00:20:25,362
Doesn't that pose
a potential problem for us?

202
00:20:25,469 --> 00:20:28,549
So does a prison term.

203
00:20:28,653 --> 00:20:32,084
Bottom line is, we got away clean.

204
00:20:35,822 --> 00:20:38,070
What's the matter, Angela?

205
00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:40,603
Don't you trust me anymore?

206
00:20:47,396 --> 00:20:49,292
Look at me.

207
00:20:51,993 --> 00:20:54,372
That kid knew my name.

208
00:20:54,469 --> 00:20:58,230
That's dangerous for all of us.

209
00:20:58,328 --> 00:21:02,207
Baby, is there anything in these eyes that
makes you think I could ever hurt you?

210
00:21:07,780 --> 00:21:09,731
[Cell Phone Ringing]

211
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:18,356
- What?
- [Man] Let's forget about what
you did to our guy in the vault.

212
00:21:18,455 --> 00:21:22,435
You killed two cops today,
and that's a problem.

213
00:21:22,537 --> 00:21:24,369
Don't start with me.

214
00:21:24,467 --> 00:21:26,780
You arrogant bastard.
You've lost control.

215
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:29,126
That's where you're wrong, my friend.

216
00:21:29,225 --> 00:21:31,440
You see...

217
00:21:33,985 --> 00:21:37,098
- I've gained control.
- Is that right?

218
00:21:37,199 --> 00:21:39,578
You bet your ass that's right.

219
00:21:39,676 --> 00:21:42,557
What's the matter with you, Rome?
Have you lost your mind?

220
00:21:42,665 --> 00:21:44,781
Have you forgotten
who you're talking to?

221
00:21:44,884 --> 00:21:47,646
I know exactly who I'm talking to.

222
00:21:47,745 --> 00:21:50,988
You see, I have the diamonds.
Therefore, I have the power.

223
00:21:51,088 --> 00:21:54,268
You have no idea of the level of hell
I could bring down on you.

224
00:21:54,369 --> 00:21:57,765
Yeah, but you won't,
not if you wanna see these diamonds.

225
00:21:57,871 --> 00:22:01,666
Tomorrow, noon. I get my diamonds,
you get your money.

226
00:22:01,763 --> 00:22:04,107
[Thunder Rumbling]

227
00:22:04,206 --> 00:22:06,002
[Beeps Off]

228
00:22:15,844 --> 00:22:20,406
Listen. About what happened at work today-

229
00:22:20,508 --> 00:22:23,236
I'm not tellin' anybody.

230
00:22:23,335 --> 00:22:25,232
Cool.

231
00:22:37,805 --> 00:22:40,237
- Hey, baby.
- Hey.

232
00:22:40,343 --> 00:22:42,975
- How was work?
- Fine.

233
00:22:43,078 --> 00:22:46,706
Yeah? What? What happened?

234
00:22:46,807 --> 00:22:49,919
- Talk to me.
- Nothing.

235
00:22:50,987 --> 00:22:52,686
Stuff.

236
00:22:52,787 --> 00:22:54,968
[Man On TV]
They're hired to protect us.

237
00:22:55,069 --> 00:22:57,601
But who will protect us from them?

238
00:22:57,706 --> 00:23:01,301
- Security guards out of control tonight at 11:00.
- Mmm.

239
00:23:01,404 --> 00:23:04,868
"Stuff." Like you throwing
a guy out of a window?

240
00:23:04,972 --> 00:23:07,471
Yeah.

241
00:23:08,670 --> 00:23:10,566
[TVShuts Off]

242
00:23:10,664 --> 00:23:14,257
I thought my days of worrying
about you were over.

243
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:17,670
- What happened?
- [Sighs]

244
00:23:17,768 --> 00:23:21,364
- This isn't me.
- Well, you jumped into work
the minute you got back.

245
00:23:21,467 --> 00:23:26,190
Kate, what was I supposed to do?
Come home, sit around?

246
00:23:26,288 --> 00:23:29,467
- That's not me. I can't do that.
- I know you can't.

247
00:23:31,176 --> 00:23:34,256
- What if we just took off?
- What?

248
00:23:34,357 --> 00:23:37,723
